records.field_99:
ParcelExplorer is a searchable parcel information database, which integrates property parcels, transportation parcels, easements, remainder parcels, and historic and scanned registry maps. Users search by street address or registry map number to identify specific parcels and access important related property data useful for identifying value and real-estate trends. Other features include the ability to measure parcels and lines, add annotation to the maps, and display a printable copy. Data for the map tool is from City of Philadelphia Department of Records' (DOR) tax maps, historic maps from the Free Library and property records from the Office of Property Assessment. Data from PhilaDox database is updated quarterly.

Usage: Public Use; Requires subscription ($30/1 month of unlimited access, $20/7 days of unlimited access, $12/1 day of unlimited access)

records.field_99:
Index that tracks changes in the names of Philadelphia streets dating back to the 1700s. The data was compiled from resources at the Philadelphia City Archives including road records, docket books, jury decisions, and surveys. The index can be searched by street name and includes information on the old and new name of the street, the recorded year of the change, and the location effected by the change.

For more information, contact the Department of Records at info@phillyhistory.org or 215-686-2260.

records.field_99:
From the document: "This report was issued in compliance with the Philadelphia Home Rule Charter (Charter), which requires that the Director of Finance “Issue within one hundred and twenty days after the close of each fiscal year a statement as of the end of that year showing the balances in all funds of the City, the amounts of the City’s known liabilities, and such other information as is necessary to furnish a true picture of the City’s financial condition”. This report is intended to meet these requirements and is not audited. The Comprehensive Annual Financial Report will be published at a later date.

The report contains financial statements for all City governmental funds and blended component units presented on the modified accrual basis. The proprietary and fiduciary funds are presented on the full accrual basis. It also contains budgetary comparison schedules for those funds that are subject to an annual budget. The financial statements of the City’s discretely presented component units that were available as of the date of this report are also presented."
